Citation: links or references to data.
hallucination : incorrect confident response from LLMs.
grounded response (avoid hallucinate for Accuracy & Reliability:):
    In artificial intelligence, grounding is the process of anchoring a model's responses to verifiable,
    real-world information rather than letting it rely solely on the statistical patterns it learned during traing
  We separate retrieval from reasoning and enforce grounding at the prompt level to prevent hallucinations.

overlaps: add 10 to 20 at end of each chunk and beginning of the chunk to avoid hallucinations.
Guardrails: SUCH AS low, high, HITS EMPTY..ETC move to fall back
// 1. get hits
// 2. best score check
// 3. topText = hits[0]
// 4. keyword guardrail (topText only)
// 5. build multi-chunk context
// 6. call LLM

getBestScore() → score extraction
passesMinimumThreshold() → low-score rejection
passesKeywordGuard() → top-1 validation
selectUsableHits() → choose top-K usable chunks
extractContextChunks() → build LLM context
extractChunkIds() → build trace ids
fallback() → standard refusal response

FAISS (Facebook AI Similarity Search): store vectors. used to search dense vector by passing embedded query, replaced cosine similarity (angle) to
Euclidean distance (magnitude, distance between points).
Euclidean distance: is best for image recognization or any data size of the values are matter. it has 2 metrics, l2, inner product.
                    Inner product usefull such as suggesting movie based on history.
FAISS: stores Vector data.
Chroma: open source Vector DB. stores, original text, meta data, vectors. has build in models like OpenAI to turn text to embeddings.


